Utilizar PANCs na alimentação traz diversos benefícios, incluindo: Diversidade nutricional: Muitas PANCs são ricas em nutrientes, como vitaminas, minerais e antioxidantes, contribuindo para uma alimentação mais variada e saudável. Resiliência e sustentabilidade: Cultivar e consumir PANCs promove a diversificação de cultivos, o que pode aumentar a resiliência dos sistemas agrícolas e reduzir a dependência de monoculturas. Conservação da biodiversidade: Ao incluir PANCs na alimentação, ajuda-se a preservar a diversidade de espécies vegetais, muitas das quais estão em risco de extinção devido à perda de habitat e à agricultura intensiva. Portanto, integrar PANCs na alimentação não só amplia a diversidade nutricional, mas também promove a sustentabilidade ambiental, a conservação da biodiversidade e o resgate cultural, enquanto oferece oportunidades para inovação gastronômica. Lista de espécies vegetais utilizadas neste almoço:  * Clitoria ternatea (flor) * Moringa oleifera (flor e folha) * Trichanthera gigantea (Madre de água) * Allium tuberosum (Nirá) * Citrus hystrix (Folha de limão kaffir) Siga @triibo.smg e @barbienaestrada para mais sobre voluntariado e agroecologia ♻️🌱✨ #viajante #viagem #natureza #nature #mochilão #Worldpackersbrasil #voluntariado #ecoturismo #ecology #biology #mochileira #worldpackers #dicas #cultura #ecopacker #saudável #DigitalNomad | #NomadLife #RemoteWork | #TravelLife #Wanderlust | #ExploreNature #Wanderlust | #ExploreNature #EcoTravel | #SustainableTravel #BackpackingLife #biomasbrasileiros #agroecologia #agroecoly #pancs

TOP must visit villages in Puglia, the perfect slow travel destination🕊️ 1. Ostuni, la città bianca. Its whitewashed houses and cobblestone streets create a charming and picturesque landscape.  2. Cisternino, la città delle macellerie, must visit for meat lovers and try the best bombettes in puglia 😋 3. Locorotondo, la città dei vino, whitewashed houses, narrow streets and charming wine cellars, paradise for wine enthusiasts.  4. Alberobello, la città dei trulli, UNESCO heritage site, a fairytale-like village full of its distinctive trully houses 🛖 5. Polignano a mare, la città più accogliente al mondo 🫶 stunning turquoise waters, hidden coves and limestone cliffs, a true gem of puglia’s coastline Which one is your favourite? 🌟 Arbeiten, wo andere Urlaub machen?  Klingt wie ein Traum?  Ich zeige dir, wie es geht! 🌟 Viele sehen das Konzept des Arbeitens an exotischen Orten mit Skepsis: Ist es wirklich produktiv?  Wie balanciert man Arbeit und Entspannung? Hier ist meine Erfahrung und wie ich es schaffe, produktiv zu bleiben, während ich die Welt erkunde:  1. Struktur ist alles: Ich beginne meinen Tag früh und folge einem festen Zeitplan – Arbeit ist Arbeit, auch im Paradies!  2. Technologie nutzen: Zuverlässiges Internet und digitale Tools sind meine besten Freunde.  3. Ich arbeite auch wenn ich am Strand sitze und mein Team mich brauch , oder ich neue Anfragen bekomme ,um euch zu zeigen ,das es jeder von euch kann .  4. Ich bau mir etwas nebenbei auf , weil das Thema ,mit 64 in Rente zu gehen , keine Option für mich ist .  Heutzutage muss man sich sehr gut um sich selber kümmern und am besten nichts erwarten was nicht in deiner Macht liegt .  💭 Was denkst du über das Arbeiten an Urlaubsorten? Eine Traumvorstellung oder eine echte Möglichkeit, Arbeit und Leben zu kombinieren? Lass es uns in den Kommentaren diskutieren! 🌍👩‍💻 #DigitalNomad #WorkFromAnywhere #RemoteWork #TravelWhileWorking #LifeWorkBalance #SustainableTravel

Hay un lugar que tardé muchos años de visitar, tal vez más de los que debí. Taxco, Guerrero. Este lugar en Guerrero, denominado Pueblo Mágico en el año 2002 es uno de esos lugares que parecen sacados de la imaginación de algún escritor. Un pueblo entre montañas, con callejones, iglesias y pasadizos ocultos. 🌮 Aunque es famoso por su joyería en plata, yo quedé profundamente enamorado de su gastronomía, desde su mole verde hasta sus tacos acorazados y sus platillos con insectos como los Jumiles.  Al igual que otras ciudades de México (Como Ganauato), Taxco ofrece unas vistas impresionantes y siempre distintas en cada esquina, la topografía de su territorio hace que sus calles empinadas sean un reto para caminar, aunque los "vochitos" viejos escarabajos Volkswagen convertidos en taxis, suben, bajan y dan vueltas  por toda la ciudad con poco esfuerzo.  Taxco es uno de esos sitios a los que siempre quiero regresar. #taxco #méxico #turismosostenible #guerrero #sustainabletravel #turismoregenerativo

It’s one of the questions we get asked the most….”what temperature are the pools?” 🌡 I’m not talking about spa’s where you can expect the pools to be a little warmer or even hot, I mean the main resort pools, where you may want to take a morning swim or play with the kids in the water and the temperature is more important to people than I think some hotels realise. As someone who feels actual pain when cold water touches my skin 🤣 I understand…I won’t get in a cooler pool unless it’s absolutely boiling outside and if the temperatures are cooler outside, the pool has to be warm! This is why we absolutely love @iberostarbeachfront hotels. Everywhere we go, they have a number of pools with a variety of different temperatures to suit different preferences and this one in particular in the centre of Iberostar Selection Anthelia, was like a luke warm bath ☺️ Especially in Europe where temperatures are not always soaring and the sun may not always be shining in the Winter months, a warm pool can make such a difference to your holiday… …these views aren’t bad either 😍 What about you? Time for your next adventure ⛰️🇦🇹 📍Ischgl, Austria If you are traveling to Austria this is one adventure you do not want to miss out on.  The Skyfly is a trio of ziplines that start at 1.683 meters high and end in the village of Ischgl at 1.376 meters. Spanning 2 kilometers, the Skyfly reaches speeds of up to 84 km/h, descending from the Silvrettabahn mid-station down to the valley in Ischgl. Address: Pardatsch-Idalpe 1, 6561 Ischgl, Austria  Opening hours: Tue-Sun: 11 am - 6 pm  Price: €39 (US$42) per adult; €25 (US$26) per child.  #austria #ischgl #tyrol #tyrolean #alps #outdoorlover #outdooradventures #outdoor #sustainabletravel #europe #sustainabletraveltips

The best ethical places to swim with whale sharks In the world 🌎 🌎🌎🌎 Swimming with whale sharks can be an incredible experience, but it's essential to choose locations that prioritize ethical and sustainable interactions. Here are some of the best ethical places to swim with whale sharks around the world:  • Isla Holbox, Mexico:  • Whale shark season: June to September.  • Regulations limit the number of boats and swimmers to minimize stress on the animals.  • Guides are trained to ensure interactions are respectful and non-intrusive.  • Ningaloo Reef, Australia:  • Whale shark season: March to July.  • Strict regulations and permits control the number of visitors.  • Operators follow guidelines to ensure minimal impact on whale sharks.  • Gladden Spit, Belize:  • Whale shark season: April to June (around the full moon).  • Limited number of licenses for operators, ensuring controlled and respectful interactions.  • The area is a marine reserve, providing additional protection for marine life.  • Donsol, Philippines:  • Whale shark season: November to June.  • Community-led tourism with strict guidelines to protect the sharks.  • No feeding or baiting; encounters are in the sharks' natural environment.  • Tofo Beach, Mozambique:  • Whale shark season: October to March.  • Research and conservation efforts support sustainable tourism practices.  • Encounters are regulated to ensure the well-being of the animals.  • Dhigurah, Maldives:  • Whale shark season: Year-round, with a peak from August to November.  • The Maldives Whale Shark Research Programme promotes ethical tourism and conservation.  • Strict regulations and community involvement in tourism management.  • Socorro Island, Mexico:  • Whale shark season: November to June.  • The island is part of a protected marine biosphere reserve.  • Tours are heavily regulated to ensure minimal disruption to marine life.  When choosing a tour operator, look for certifications or affiliations with conservation organizations, adherence to local regulations, and a clear commitment to sustainable practices. This helps ensure that your experience contributes to the protection and preservation of whale sharks and their habitats.  #swimwithwhalesharks  #whalesharkadventure  #EthicalTravel #MarineConservation #sustainabletourism  #whalesharkencounter  #protectouroceans  #OceanConservation  #wildliferespect  #ecofriendlytravel  #marinelifelover  #wildlifephotography  #responsibletravel  #whalesharkseason  #underwaterworld  #savethewhalesharks  #MarineBiodiversity #sustainabletravel  #WhaleShark  #marinewildlife

From Lake Titikaka to Panama in under one month!⚡️ As the Pacific Ocean crossing season is closer to an end, especially with cyclones lurking, especially in the South Pacific and considering other hazards, our goal is to reach Shelters Bay on Panama’s Atlantic Coast before end of May. There, we aim to join a crew headed west across the Pacific. But the journey isn’t straightforward without flights.🌊 Firstly, we’re keen on exploring landscapes and sustainable initiatives on the road. Secondly, Ecuador’s land entry poses challenges due to its political turbulence. Lastly, without a road linking Colombia and Panama, our route requires finding a boat for passage! 🏝️ Did You Know? The Maldives 🌊 This tropical paradise has over 2,500 years of history! Once a key stop on ancient trade routes, it’s rich in cultural influences—from Buddhism and Hinduism to Islam. 🕌 But there’s more—these islands are among the lowest-lying in the world, making them a symbol in the fight against climate change. 🌍 So, next time you think of the Maldives, remember—there’s deep history beneath that beauty! ✨ #Maldives #TropicalParadise #History #IslandLife #SustainableTravel

🐘 A new study based on more than 100 elephants in Amboseli National Park and Samburu National Reserve in Kenya as quoted in Nature Ecology and Evolution has revealed that Elephants may use name-like calls to address each other highlighting their advanced social bonds and communication skills. Researchers noticed that when an elephant makes a vocalization to a group of other elephants, all of them respond but sometimes when that same elephant makes a similar call to the group, only a single individual responds.  #beingavoiceforwildlife #samburunationalreserve  #kenyansafari #uniqueplaces #placestovisit #adventuretravel #bucketlisttrip #travelmore #wildlifeonearth #sustainabletravel #bucketlistadventures #safari #wildlifetiktok #africansafari #didyouknow #wildlifesafari   #wildlifereels #elephantlovers #elephantfacts #elephantsoftiktok #traveltheworld #samburu #earthfocus #uktravelblogger #didyouknowfacts #connectwithnature  Facts | Elephants | wildlife | Samburu | kenya | safari | africa | african wildlife | african elephants | did you know | friendship | inspirational | motivational | Elephants Kenya | Unusual facts

🌊Today is #WorldOceansDay and these are videos I have taken myself on my travels which shows glimpses of the unprecedented levels of pollution of “the Earth’s lungs” and damage to one of the planet’s most important aids in fighting climate change.  Did you know that approximately 19 to 23 million tons of plastic end up in the water every year, and this number is forecasted to treble by 2040?  Plastic pollution kills wildlife, damages natural ecosystems, and contributes to climate change. The problem with plastic is that most of it is not biodegradable. It doesn’t rot, like paper or food, so instead it can hang around in the environment and take hundreds of years to break down. According to research released last year, oceans across the world have also reached record high temperatures. Seas are now warmer than at any other time in recorded human history and the increase in temperature has been directly linked to global warming. Little things we can do is clean up beaches whenever we see rubbish and switch from using single use plastics.  Never feel like a tiny action won’t make a difference because it will. We need to do better together! #worldoceansday2024 #oceans #saveouroceans #oceanpollution #oceanpollutionawareness #oceanpollutioncontrol #plasticpollution #responsibletravel #sustainabletravel #oceanlover #oceanlove #cleanoceans #oceansday #savetheocean #savetheoceans #worldoceanday
